This bootstrap repository contains architecture documentation and Kotlin
skeleton code for a GNSS receiver recorder, NTRIP client, correction router,
receiver controller and base-calibration workflow companion.

Third-party dependencies must be documented in docs/third-party-licenses.md
before release builds are distributed.

RTKLIB-EX real-time integration uses Android native build glue and a pinned
local checkout created by tools/update_rtklib_ex.py. The current pinned
development commit is 8dfabc9a106b2e74c069bc80f0d7743f314e6ab4 from
https://github.com/rtklibexplorer/RTKLIB.git. The upstream checkout is ignored
by Git, but Android release artifacts that include librtkcollector_rtklib.so
must preserve the RTKLIB BSD 2-clause licence text, upstream copyright notices
and the corresponding source/reproducibility information recorded under
third_party/rtklib-ex/.
